{"tid":906613,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"欲影響公報內容 4中國官員被趕出巴布亞新幾內亞外交部","createTime":"2018-11-18T06:45:09.000Z","updateTime":"2018-11-18T07:42:47.000Z","uid":41404,"like":9,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":7,"replies":[{"pid":"0fbc08aa9c35d09c7ef541c7b41dd4ad760cd634","tid":906613,"uid":41404,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-11-18T06:45:09.000Z","msg":"正在巴布亞新幾內亞（簡稱巴新）舉行的亞太經濟合作組織（APEC）峯會，籠罩在中美對峙的氣氛中。繼中國國家主席習近平與美國副總統彭斯（Mike Pence）昨各自演說中針鋒相對後，今天又傳出有中方官員試圖闖入巴新外交部長辦公室，企圖影響草擬中的峯會公報內容，惹得巴新當局驅趕4名中國官員，派出警察駐守在外交部長辦公室外。<br />\n法新社、《澳洲人報》等媒體引述至少3名消息人士報道，有4名中國代表團成員昨天（17日）赴巴新外交部，要求會見外交部長披圖（Rimbink Pato），企圖在最後一刻影響峯會公報內容。<br />\n<br />\n披圖的發言人指出，當時披圖在辦公室內，但認為不宜單獨與中方協商，因此拒絕與他們會晤，4名中方官員因而遭逐出巴新外交部。有消息人士指出，「中方協商人士早就清楚」，披圖不願和他們見面，但執意前往披圖的辦公室。巴新外交部也表示，外長只會見其他國家的外長。<br />\n<br />\n面對法新社求證時，披圖低調回應稱此事「不構成問題」，中方代表團尚未回應此事。APEC峯會通常會達成共同聲明，但今年因中美貿易爭議激烈，官員承認恐怕無法發佈正式公報。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://hk.news.appledaily.com/china/realtime/article/20181118/58927984\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fhk.news.appledaily.com%2Fchina%2Frealtime%2Farticle%2F20181118%2F58927984&d=6tuXhv1Op5ZcMF%2FNsQcJwJ4%2BuNhYgvPKbWZYs3KJomg%3D&h=b0d44dca\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fhk.news.appledaily.com%2Fchina%2Frealtime%2Farticle%2F20181118%2F58927984&h=2aa2243c\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://hk.news.appledaily.com/china/realtime/article/20181118/58927984</a>"},{"pid":"de07e8508110e9dcb82a0b9cbbfcea81636ae822","tid":906613,"uid":41404,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-11-18T07:01:04.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-11-18/chinese-officials-create-diplomatic-storm-at-apec/10508812\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fnews%2F2018-11-18%2Fchinese-officials-create-diplomatic-storm-at-apec%2F10508812&d=6tuXhv1Op5ZcMF%2FNsQcJwJ4%2BuNhYgvPKbWZYs3KJomg%3D&h=ce5817b8\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-11-18/chinese-officials-create-diplomatic-storm-at-apec/10508812</a><br />\n<br />\nFour Chinese officials barged into the office of Papua New Guinea's Foreign Minister Rimbink Pato on Saturday afternoon after being denied a meeting.<br />\n<br />\nThe ABC understands the Chinese Senior Officials Meeting negotiators wanted to meet with the Minister to discuss the wording of the APEC final communique.<br />\n<br />\nWhen they were repeatedly denied a meeting they pushed their way into Mr Pato's office, calling out to the Minister for two minutes of his time.<br />\n<br />\nSecurity was called to the office and the officials had to be forced from the room.<br />\n<br />\nThe officials eventually left of their own accord."},{"pid":"bfb0b2a50f72377e46f31632d95afe8efe80e050","tid":906613,"uid":37528,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-11-18T07:05:00.000Z","msg":"其實支那人個腦入面諗乜架<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"31c38884c0fa0008e2415c83ed21185cf7d35aa0","tid":906613,"uid":18912,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-11-18T07:05:34.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bang.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b5fed16c8a786be046b119f1c1e5f464ff07bfbf","tid":906613,"uid":19527,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-11-18T07:08:41.000Z","msg":"又贏<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b37a6d731bc1af08d761e92f41990ffc43c19e46","tid":906613,"uid":49588,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-11-18T07:20:27.000Z","msg":"中國特色行動<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"796a1dc611b742f98a73adef0988e23b008e7efa","tid":906613,"uid":18955,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,